---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Kitchen Explored" description="Kitchen Explored publishes honest, hands-on kitchen appliance comparisons. Learn who we are and how we test.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-[1344px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <p class="text-orange-start text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">About Us</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight max-w-2xl mb-6">
        Honest comparisons for people who cook.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-white/60 text-lg max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
        Kitchen Explored exists because most appliance reviews online are vague, affiliate-first, and written by people who have never actually used the product.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <div class="max-w-[1344px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 py-16">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-16">

      <!-- Left: long-form text -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none prose-headings:text-navy prose-headings:font-bold prose-a:text-orange-start prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline">

          <h2>Why we started this site</h2>
          <p>
            I'm Matt Hickman. I started Kitchen Explored in 2022 after spending an embarrassing amount
            of time trying to figure out whether a $600 Vitamix was actually worth it over a $90 Ninja.
            Every article I found was either a thinly veiled Amazon listing or a top-ten list with zero
            real comparison.
          </p>
          <p>
            So I started writing the comparisons I wished existed — specific, structured, and honest
            about trade-offs. The site now covers over 180 head-to-head matchups across blenders,
            cookware, knives, ovens, pressure cookers, and kitchen faucets.
          </p>

          <h2>How we research and write</h2>
          <p>
            Every article follows the same structure: we start with the specs that actually matter
            (motor wattage, material construction, warranty terms), then move to real-world factors
            like noise, ease of cleaning, and long-term durability based on owner reports and
            hands-on use.
          </p>
          <p>
            We don't pad articles with generic kitchen trivia. If a product is worse in a specific
            way, we say so. The comparison tables on each page are designed to let you see the
            differences at a glance without reading the whole article.
          </p>

          <h2>Affiliate links — here's how that works</h2>
          <p>
            Most product links on this site go to Amazon and are affiliate links. If you buy
            something after clicking, we earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. This is
            how the site pays for itself.
          </p>
          <p>
            That said, affiliate revenue does not influence which product we recommend. We recommend
            the better product. If the cheaper one wins, we say so. If neither is worth buying, we
            say that too.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: stat cards + author bio -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">

        <!-- Author card -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-100 p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-navy text-white flex items-center justify-center text-base font-bold shrink-0">MH</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">Matt Hickman</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Founder, Kitchen Explored</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Home cook and kitchen obsessive based in the US. Testing appliances since 2022,
            cooking for far longer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stats -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-100 p-6 flex flex-col gap-5">
          {[
            { number: '180+', label: 'Appliance comparisons published' },
            { number: '6', label: 'Categories covered' },
            { number: '2022', label: 'Year we launched' },
          ].map(s => (
            <div>
              <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy">{s.number}</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-0.5">{s.label}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <!-- Categories -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-100 p-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">What we cover</p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {['Blenders', 'Cookware', 'Knives', 'Ovens', 'Pressure Cookers', 'Faucets'].map(c => (
              <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-gray-100 text-gray-700">{c}</span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <div class="border-t border-gray-100 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-[1344px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 py-12 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-navy text-lg">Have a product you'd like us to compare?</p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-1">Reach out — we read every email.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/contact/" class="shrink-0 px-6 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-white font-semibold text-sm whitespace-nowrap" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#f78745,#f85026)">
        Get in Touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
